# SingleCourseWebApp Template Documentation

This document provides a comprehensive guide to the template (html) files in the SingleCourseWebApp Django application, including their relationships with JavaScript and CSS files. The data passed into these template files come from views.py.

## Template Structure Overview

The templates in this application follow a hierarchical structure:

```
course/templates/course/
├── adminpage/                # Admin interface templates
├── editcourse/               # Course management templates
├── homepage/                 # Home page templates
├── learningpage/             # Learning interface templates
│   └── lesson_types/         # Specific lesson type templates
└── submissions/              # Submission management templates
```

## Template-JavaScript-CSS Relationships

### 2. Course Management

#### 2.1 Management Base

**Template:** `course/templates/course/editcourse/management_base.html`

**Description:** Base template for all course management pages. Provides the common layout and navigation.

**CSS Dependencies:**
- `course/static/course/css/management.css`
  - Styling for management navigation
  - Styling for management layout

**Data Context:**
- `course`: Course object being managed

#### 2.2 Module Management

**Template:** `course/templates/course/editcourse/manage_modules.html`

**Description:** Interface for managing course modules and lessons.

**JavaScript Dependencies:**
- `course/static/course/js/manage-modules.js`
  - `ModuleManager`: Handles module CRUD operations
  - `LessonManager`: Handles lesson CRUD operations
  - `DragDropManager`: Provides drag-and-drop reordering

**CSS Dependencies:**
- `course/static/course/css/manage-modules.css`
  - Styling for module cards
  - Styling for lesson items
  - Styling for drag-and-drop functionality

**Data Context:**
- `course`: Course object being managed
- `modules`: List of module objects
- `csrf_token`: CSRF token for form submission

#### 2.3 Course Settings

**Template:** `course/templates/course/editcourse/manage_settings.html`

**Description:** Interface for managing course settings.

**JavaScript Dependencies:**
- `course/static/course/js/manage-settings.js`
  - Handles form submission
  - Manages course settings updates

**CSS Dependencies:**
- `course/static/course/css/management.css`
  - Styling for settings forms

**Data Context:**
- `course`: Course object being managed
- `form`: Form object for course settings

#### 2.4 Group Management

**Template:** `course/templates/course/editcourse/manage_groups.html`

**Description:** Interface for managing student groups.

**CSS Dependencies:**
- `course/static/course/css/manage_groups.css`
  - Styling for group cards
  - Styling for member lists
  - Styling for group actions

**Data Context:**
- `course`: Course object being managed
- `groups`: List of group objects
- `students`: List of student objects
